# wxops bootstrap (read before acting)

Applies when the task mentions **wxops**, **wxcli**, **Webex Calling**, **CDR**, **devices**, **call control**, **WebRTC**, **voicemail**, **billing**, or paths under `wxops/`.

## Mandatory first reads (in order)

1. `~/Documents/GitHub/CLAUDE.md` — OAuth, tokens, MCP, cross-project routing
2. `~/Documents/GitHub/wxops/CLAUDE.md` — playbook, skill map, `wxcli` → wxcadm → HTTP pattern
3. **`~/Documents/GitHub/.cursor/wxops-session-context.md`** — living summary of what we built, fixed, IDs, and lessons (read fully; do not skip)
4. **One skill** from `wxops/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` (see routing below)
5. **Reference docs** that skill points to under `wxops/docs/reference/` — read before API/CLI calls

Do **not** improvise flows (e.g. ad-hoc scripts) until steps 1–5 are done. Use **wxops MCP** `wxops_run_command` or `wxcli` per the skill — not guessed endpoints.

**After completing significant wxops work:** update `wxops-session-context.md` (new fixes, IDs, scripts, gotchas) and bump *Last updated*.

